examples.en: We warmed ourselves by the fire.
I built a fire, warmed up, and dried my clothes out.
The room was warmed by a brazier.
We warmed our hands over the fire.
The sun warmed up the seat nicely.
The soup warmed slowly on the stove.
He took out his strap and warmed him.
He warmed his hands in front of the fire.
When air is warmed it expands and becomes lighter.
They warmed up for U2 on one of their early tours.
The guitarist warmed up with a few simple arpeggios.
They sat on the hearth and warmed themselves before the fire.
His heart warmed over Baretti as they walked along together. (D. C. Murray)
As he warmed to his subject, he infected his listeners with his own excitement.
The unfriendly looks quickly warmed when we were recognized as long-unseen relatives.
